<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PrimarySourceReference/159> rdfs:label "Primary Source Reference: #159" ;
	a dprr:PrimarySourceReference ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Auct. vir. ill. 57.4" ;
	dprr:forAssertion <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/155> .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/277> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #277" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to negotiate with the plebeians who had seceded to the Aventine (Liv. 3.50.15-16; Ascon. 77 C)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/260> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #260" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Prepared and caused the enactment of ten tables of laws (Cic. Rep. 2.61; Liv. 3.33.1-36.2; Diod. 12.23.1; Dion. Hal. 10.56.1-2; Tac. Ann. 3.27; Gell. 11.18.6; 17.21.15; 20.1; Dig. 1.2.2.3-4 and 24; Zon. 7.18)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/252> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #252" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Diod. preserves all or part of eight names, omitting Sestius and Curiatius, Fast. Cap. all or part of six with space for the rest, those of Sestius, Curiatius, Romilius and Postumius, which are supplied from the information on their consulships (Degrassi 26f., 94, 364f.). According to Dion. Hal. (10.56.2) they were all consulars, but this principle was not applied consistently in Livy or Fast. Cap. See notes 3 and 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/115> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #115" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 2.43.1; Fast. Cap. ([- - - -] Vibulanus II); Dion. Hal. 8.90.5, cf. 10.56.2; Chr. 354 (Pelos et Vibulano II); Fast. Hyd. (Tertullo et Fabio II), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Lyd. Magg. 1.38; on Iulius, Ascon. 76 C. See Degrassi 24f., 89, 354f. Livy and Dion. Hal. mention fighting with Aequi and Veientani." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/114> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #114" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These Consuls are omitted in Diodorus. Livy (2.43.1, see apparatus in Conway and Walters edition) has the reading C. Tullius, but Dion. Hal., Cassiod., and Fast. Cap. under 451 furnish the correct forms. On his filiation, see Fast. Cap. under 451, Degrassi 27, and on the cognomen Iullus, see 489, note 2." .
